subject: Golf
lead_paragraph: Lorena Ochoa, who is trying to win her fourth consecutive tournament, shot a five-under-par 67 on Friday in the second round of the Ginn Open at Reunion, Fla. Ochoa is three strokes behind the leader, Yani Tseng. Tseng moved to 12 under with a course-record 64. Suzann Pettersen (66) was 10 under, a shot ahead of Ochoa and Minea Blomqvist (66).
